Information
------------------------------

Europe Under Attack
On Tuesday, terrorists attacked Brussels leaving more than 30 dead and hundreds wounded - just four months after the atrocities in Paris. Julie Etchingham reports from a city still reeling in shock, questions the implications for Europe's security, borders and political future, and asks, as millions of Britons prepare to fly abroad for their Easter break, what this recurrence of violence means for the whole of Europe.
